      "question": "If $1/2$ is a root of the equation $x^2 - kx - 5/4 = 0$, then the value of $k$ is:",
      "answer": "(D)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Substitute $x = 1/2$ into the equation.",
          "$(1/2)^2 - k(1/2) - 5/4 = 0$.",
          "$1/4 - k/2 - 5/4 = 0 \\implies -4/4 - k/2 = 0 \\implies -1 = k/2 \\implies k = -2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right)^2 - k\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right) - \\frac{5}{4} = 0 \\implies \\frac{1}{4} - \\frac{k}{2} - \\frac{5}{4} = 0 \\implies -1 - \\frac{k}{2} = 0 \\implies k = -2"
      },
